// pyth `update_*` exact shape: a staleness check is `if (a>b) { if (a-b>=thr) {fail; goto J} }
// else { if (b-a>=thr) {fail; goto J} }`. The inner threshold-ifs both fall through to the
// SAME next node (4) on success, and both fail-arms (3,5) jump to the far join (7).
//
//   0 cond(a>b) ─true─> 1 cond(thr) ─true─> 3 (fail; goto 7)
//   │ false             │ false
//   │                   v
//   │                   4 (fallthrough/rest; goto 7)
//   v                   ^
//   2 cond(thr) ─true─> 5 (fail; goto 7)
//   │ false ────────────┘
//   v
//   (2's false also goes to 4)
//   7 (join, sink)
//
// 4.idom = 0 (reached from 1.else and 2.else). 7.idom = 0. Does the inner `goto 7` survive?
cond,0,1,2
cond,1,3,4
cond,2,5,4
code,3,7
code,5,7
code,4,7
code,7
